12 (d) A license granted pursuant to this act shall not be sold or transferred by the licensee.
13 If a licensee terminates or fails to renew a license granted under this act, or any such license is
14 cancelled, revoked or no longer in use, the license shall be returned physically, with all of the
15 legal rights, privileges and restrictions pertaining thereto, to the licensing authority of the town of
16 Scituate, which may then grant the license to a new applicant under the same conditions as
17 specified in this section.
18 (e) All licenses granted under this section shall be issued within 3 years after the effective
19 date of this act; provided, however, that a license originally granted within that time period may
20 be granted to a new applicant under subsection (d) thereafter.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon its passage.
